Release Notes
Dskyz (DAFE) GENESIS: Adaptive Quant, Real Regime Power

GENESIS is not a template or a black-box mashup. It’s DAFE’s own adaptive, multi-factor, regime-aware quant engine—built to outperform, survive, and visualize live edge in anything from NQ/MNQ to stocks and crypto.

What Makes This Strategy Unique
True multi-factor core: Volume/price imbalances, trend shifts, volatility compression/expansion, and RSI all interlock for signal creation.
Adaptive regime logic: Trades only in healthy, actionable conditions—no “one-size-fits-all” signals.
Momentum normalization: Uses rolling, percentile-based fast/slow EMA differentials, always normalized and relevant.
Adaptive position sizing: Not fixed-lot, not naive—position size adapts to regime and volatility.
No hidden DCA or pyramiding: What you see is what you trade.
Dashboard and visuals: All stats and visuals are directly connected to the internal logic—no cosmetic overlays.

Backtest Settings:
Initial capital: $10,000
Commission: 12.50 perside
12.50perside,25 round-trip per contract (covers exchange, broker, and slippage)
Slippage: 3 ticks per trade (NQ = $15 per contract per trade)
Order size: Adaptive, 1–3 contracts
Max risk per trade: $750 (7.5% of capital)
Symbol: CME_MINI:NQ1!
Timeframe: 1 min (works on all timeframes)
No pyramiding, no hidden DCA
Sample size: Designed to generate >100 trades for robust statistics (if your filters are strict and you get fewer, explain why in your notes).

Why these settings?
These settings are intentionally strict and realistic, reflecting the true costs and risks of live trading. If it works here, it will work in real conditions.

Inputs (Explained)
Maximum Raw Score: Number of factors contributing to regime/trade confidence (default 4).
RSI Length / Min RSI for Shorts / Max RSI for Longs: Fine-tune overbought/oversold logic.
Min Normed Momentum/Score (Conf): Filter for only the strongest trends.
ATR Lookback, ATR Low/High Percentile: Controls system’s awareness of volatility regime.
Trading Session: Filter for when entries are allowed (default: regular trading hours).
Max Dollar Risk / Base-Max Contracts: Adaptive sizing based on live regime and volatility.
Stop/Trail/Scale multipliers: ATR-based, so all risk controls and profit-taking auto-adjust to market mode.

How the Strategy Works
Signals: Combines trend, volume imbalance, RSI, and volatility regime for entries.
Adaptive Sizing: Position size adapts to regime confidence, momentum, and volatility.
Risk Management: ATR-based stops, trailing stops, and scale-outs.
No hidden pyramiding or DCA.
Visuals: Dashboard (top right) shows live stats; momentum bar (bottom right) reflects regime and momentum in real time.

How to Use
- Apply to NQ, MNQ, or any liquid stock/crypto on 1m or higher timeframe.
- Adjust risk and sizing inputs to match your account and risk tolerance.
- Use dashboard and momentum bar for live feedback on regime and trade quality.
- Backtest and paper trade before going live.

